    <h1>Amer&#xAD;i&#xAD;cans bat&#xAD;tle for top spot in Ber&#xAD;muda</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201102/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-02"><time>2020-11-02</time></a>
        - <span>SPORT</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>BER­MUDA • Doc Red­man tamed strong winds to card a four-un­der 67 and 10-un­der 203 to­tal in the third round of the Ber­muda Cham­pi­onship on Satur­day, tak­ing a one-stroke lead as he guns for his first PGA Tour win.</p>
    <p>Fel­low Amer­i­cans Ryan Ar­mour (70), Wyn­d­ham Clark (70) and Kramer Hickok (69) all lurked just one be­hind at nine-un­der.</p>
    <p>The Caribbean tour­na­ment marks the first time the Tour has al­lowed fans since the on­set of the Covid-19 pan­demic.</p>


